abstract: The Trump administration has approved a resumption of Pakistan's participation in a coveted U.S. military training and educational program more than a year after it was suspended, the State Department said on Thursday.
snippet: The Trump administration has approved a resumption of Pakistan's participation in a coveted U.S. military training and educational program more than a year after it was suspended, the State Department said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration has approved a resumption of Pakistan's participation in a coveted U.S. military training and educational program more than a year after it was suspended, the State Department said on Thursday.
headline_main: U.S. to Resume Military Training Program for Pakistan: State Department
headline_print_headline: U.S. to Resume Military Training Program for Pakistan: State Department

abstract: The magazine founded by the late Reverend Billy Graham that is influential with conservative evangelical Christians in the United States called on Thursday for President Donald Trump to be removed from office.
snippet: The magazine founded by the late Reverend Billy Graham that is influential with conservative evangelical Christians in the United States called on Thursday for President Donald Trump to be removed from office.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - The magazine founded by the late Reverend Billy Graham that is influential with conservative evangelical Christians in the United States called on Thursday for President Donald Trump to be removed from office.
headline_main: Billy Graham's Evangelical Magazine Calls for Trump's Removal
headline_print_headline: Billy Graham's Evangelical Magazine Calls for Trump's Removal

abstract: Michael Cohen, a former personal lawyer for U.S. President Donald Trump, should not be released from prison early for cooperating with authorities, federal prosecutors told a judge Thursday, saying he had repeatedly lied to them.
snippet: Michael Cohen, a former personal lawyer for U.S. President Donald Trump, should not be released from prison early for cooperating with authorities, federal prosecutors told a judge Thursday, saying he had repeatedly lied to them.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Michael Cohen, a former personal lawyer for U.S. President Donald Trump, should not be released from prison early for cooperating with authorities, federal prosecutors told a judge Thursday, saying he had repeatedly lied to them.
headline_main: Prosecutors Oppose Early Prison Release for Ex-Trump Lawyer Cohen
headline_print_headline: Prosecutors Oppose Early Prison Release for Ex-Trump Lawyer Cohen

abstract: Japan's government on Friday approved an eighth straight annual increase in defense spending to a record high as it buys U.S.-made stealth fighters, interceptor missiles and other equipment to counter military build-ups by North Korea and China.
snippet: Japan's government on Friday approved an eighth straight annual increase in defense spending to a record high as it buys U.S.-made stealth fighters, interceptor missiles and other equipment to counter military build-ups by North Korea and China....
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japan's government on Friday approved an eighth straight annual increase in defense spending to a record high as it buys U.S.-made stealth fighters, interceptor missiles and other equipment to counter military build-ups by North Korea and China.
headline_main: Japan Government Approves Eighth Straight Defense Spending Hike to Record High
headline_print_headline: Japan Government Approves Eighth Straight Defense Spending Hike to Record High

abstract: The new North American trade deal addresses most concerns of U.S. labor unions, Richard Trumka, head of the AFL-CIO union federation, said on Thursday, but even so he expects it could take more than a decade to reverse job losses resulting from the original 25-year-old trade pact.
snippet: The new North American trade deal addresses most concerns of U.S. labor unions, Richard Trumka, head of the AFL-CIO union federation, said on Thursday, but even so he expects it could take more than a decade to reverse job losses resulting from th...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The new North American trade deal addresses most concerns of U.S. labor unions, Richard Trumka, head of the AFL-CIO union federation, said on Thursday, but even so he expects it could take more than a decade to reverse job losses resulting from the original 25-year-old trade pact.
headline_main: AFL-CIO's Trumka Says USMCA Is First Step to Undoing Evils of NAFTA
headline_print_headline: AFL-CIO's Trumka Says USMCA Is First Step to Undoing Evils of NAFTA

abstract: It’s the holiday season and we’re hot and hungry. A roundup of our favorite food, wine and restaurants of late.
snippet: It’s the holiday season and we’re hot and hungry. A roundup of our favorite food, wine and restaurants of late.
lead_paragraph: It’s the holiday season and we’re hot, hungry and ready for a break — so this week’s newsletter will be short and laser-focused on what brings comfort: food and drink.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates offered two very different debates during their final forum of 2019. In the first half, they spent much of their time making the case for their electability in a contest with President Donald Trump. The second half was filled with friction over money in politics, Afghanistan and experience.

lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Democratic presidential candidates offered two very different debates during their final forum of 2019. In the first half, they spent much of their time making the case for their electability in a contest with President Donald Trump. The second half was filled with friction over money in politics, Afghanistan and experience.

abstract: Moderators asked the 2020 candidates if they agreed with an assessment made recently by former President Obama about women being better leaders and “old men” needing to get out of the way.
snippet: Moderators asked the 2020 candidates if they agreed with an assessment made recently by former President Obama about women being better leaders and “old men” needing to get out of the way.
lead_paragraph: About an hour into what was a relatively calm Democratic debate Thursday night, moderators turned up the heat by asking the 2020 candidates if they agreed with an assessment made recently by former President Barack Obama: That women should lead, and that problems arise when “old people, usually old men,” fail to get “out of the way.”

abstract: Pete Buttigieg and Elizabeth Warren have assailed each other over transparency issues in the last weeks. Their sparring intensified at the debate on Thursday.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg and Elizabeth Warren have assailed each other over transparency issues in the last weeks. Their sparring intensified at the debate on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: A fund-raiser for Pete Buttigieg held in a wine cellar in Napa Valley elicited the most strident clash between the Democratic candidates at a debate Thursday night after a mostly staid discussion of policy platforms and impeachment, leading to a round of criticism of the mayor that continued into a later exchange about his previous criticisms of Washington experience and his presidential credentials as mayor of a midsize city.
